<div class="container-fluid" id="main">
  <h2><b><i>Frequently Asked Questions</i></b></h2>
  </br>
  <h3>Q: What is Grubbery?</h3>
  <div>
    A: Grubbery is a mobile web application that helps you find meals to eat at UC San Diego's campus based on your nutritional goals and dietary preferences. On top of that, you can search for meals based on location and available time to eat. 
  </div>
  </br>
  <h3>Q: Why should I register an account with Grubbery?</h3>
  <div>
    A: By registering an account with us, you save your personal Dietary Goal and Dietary Restrictions in our system. This way, you can easily remember the nutritional goals you set for yourself, and you don't need to alter either field every time you search for food.
  </div>
  </br>
  <h3>Q: What are "Dietary Goals"?</h3>
  <div>
    A: The "Dietary Goal" feature helps you choose and set your own personal nutritional goal from our five custom preset list. Choose a nutritional goal that best fits your personal needs and future goals. Choose wisely! 
  </div>
  </br>
  <ul style="list-style-type:disc">
    <li><em>Lose Weight </em><br>You're looking to slim down a size and eat healthier. Aren't we all? Pick this goal to get meals that will do just that.</li>
    <li><em>Gain Lean Muscle</em><br>It's beach season. Every season. Pick this option for foods that will help you gain muscle.</li>
    <li><em>Gain Weight</em><br> Because you know it's all about that bass. Pick this goal if you're looking for carbs and fats.</li>
    <li><em>Maintain Weight</em><br> You're feeling just right about your weight. You go Glen Coco! Pick this option for healthy foods that won't make you skinnier or fatter. </li>
    <li><em>None</em></br> What are dietary goals? You eat to get full and that is it. Pick this option if you don't want any dietary goal filters. </li>
  </ul>
  </br>
  <h3>Q: Are the displayed nutritional facts for the meals real or accurate?</h3>
  <div>
    A: Definitely! All the nutritional information, from the ingredients to the calories to the serving sizes, represent real information on real meals that our campus dining venues serve. The nutritional information shown is exactly what is reported by each respective dining location. If you have any questions or concerns about the facts or numbers, please contact your respective dining location directly.
  </div>
